Personalized Recommendations: Use customer segmentation and predictive analytics to offer tailored product recommendations based on individual preferences and purchase history.
Customer Retention: Identify customers at risk of churn and implement targeted retention strategies to improve customer loyalty.
Customer Acquisition: Identify potential customer segments for acquisition campaigns and optimize marketing efforts for maximum ROI.
Inventory Management: Predict product demand to optimize inventory levels and reduce stockouts or overstocks.
Price Optimization: Implement dynamic pricing strategies based on customer segments and demand forecasting
Key Performance Indicators (KPIs)
Customer Lifetime Value (CLTV): Measure the overall value of a customer to the business.
Customer Acquisition Cost (CAC): Evaluate the efficiency of customer acquisition channels.
Customer Churn Rate: Track customer retention and identify areas for improvement.
Conversion Rate: Measure the effectiveness of marketing campaigns and website design.
Average Order Value (AOV): Analyze the average spending per customer.
Return on Investment (ROI): Assess the profitability of marketing campaigns and predictive models.
